# Replacing Supabase with Dedicated Clanker Cloud SQL

## Goal

Migrate Clanker from Supabase (Auth + Postgres + RPC + RLS-driven client access) to a dedicated Google Cloud SQL Postgres instance accessed only from Firebase Cloud Functions.

Important constraint: Account/Supabase schema is multi-tenant (`app_name` model). New Clanker Cloud SQL schema is single-tenant and dedicated to Clanker only.

Hard requirement: after this migration, the Clanker app, functions, tests, configs, and docs must contain no active Supabase references and no Supabase-dependent code paths.

## Final Architecture

```
React Native / Web app
                ↓
Firebase Auth (identity)
                ↓
Firebase Cloud Functions (all DB access)
                ↓
Cloud SQL PostgreSQL (Clanker only, single-tenant)
```

No client-side direct DB access. No Supabase Auth sessions. No Supabase RLS dependency.

