## Schema Strategy: Multi-tenant -> Single-tenant

### Why reshape schema

Old model stores many apps in one table (`user_app_subscriptions.app_name`).
Dedicated Clanker DB removes app discriminator entirely.

### Target schema (Cloud SQL)

Use Drizzle ORM for schema + migrations.

1. `users`
       - `id uuid pk`
       - `firebase_uid text unique not null`
       - `email text unique not null`
       - `display_name text null`
       - `avatar_url text null`
       - `is_profile_public boolean not null default false`
       - `default_character_id uuid null`
       - `created_at timestamptz`
       - `updated_at timestamptz`

2. `subscriptions`
       - `id uuid pk`
       - `user_id uuid unique not null references users(id) on delete cascade`
       - `plan_tier text not null default 'free' check in ('free','monthly_20','monthly_50','payg')`
       - `plan_status text not null default 'active' check in ('active','cancelled','expired')`
       - `current_credits integer not null default 0`
       - `terms_version text null`
       - `terms_accepted_at timestamptz null`
       - `stripe_subscription_id text null`
       - `stripe_customer_id text null`
       - `billing_cycle_start timestamptz null`
       - `billing_cycle_end timestamptz null`
       - `created_at timestamptz`
       - `updated_at timestamptz`

3. `credit_transactions`
       - `id uuid pk`
       - `user_id uuid not null references users(id) on delete cascade`
       - `delta integer not null`
       - `reason text not null`
       - `reference_id text null`
       - `created_at timestamptz`

4. `characters`
       - `id uuid pk`
       - `user_id uuid not null references users(id) on delete cascade`
       - `name text not null`
       - `avatar text null`
       - `appearance text null`
       - `traits text null`
       - `emotions text null`
       - `context text null`
       - `is_public boolean not null default false`
       - `created_at timestamptz`
       - `updated_at timestamptz`

5. `messages`
       - `id uuid pk`
       - `character_id uuid not null references characters(id) on delete cascade`
       - `sender_user_id uuid not null references users(id) on delete cascade`
       - `message_id text not null`
       - `text text not null`
       - `sender_name text null`
       - `sender_avatar text null`
       - `message_data jsonb not null default '{}'::jsonb`
       - `created_at timestamptz`

   Note: `recipient_user_id` removed — always derivable from `character_id → characters.user_id`. Clanker is user↔character chat; the recipient is always the character's owner.

### Indexes and Query Expectations

Frequent lookups and required indexes:

- `users.firebase_uid` unique index (auth/bootstrap hot path)
- `users.email` unique index (webhook/user resolution by email)
- `subscriptions.user_id` unique index (single row per user, subscription reads)
- `characters.user_id` index (list/profile character queries)
- `messages.character_id` index (chat thread/history reads)
- `messages.sender_user_id` index (moderation/debug queries by sender)
- `credit_transactions.user_id` index (credit ledger/audit reads)
- Optional composite for message timelines: `(character_id, created_at desc)`

Target SLO guardrails for initial migration validation:

- `get user by firebase_uid/email`: p95 < 50ms
- `get characters by user_id`: p95 < 100ms
- `get messages by character_id`: p95 < 120ms

### Delete Policy

- Default policy: hard delete with FK cascade (already reflected in schema)
- No `deleted_at` soft-delete columns in initial migration
- If compliance/audit requirements change, introduce soft-delete in a separate migration with explicit retention rules

### Subscription Defaults and Onboarding Credits

- New users start with `plan_tier='free'`, `plan_status='active'`, `current_credits=0`
- Onboarding credit grants are applied by service logic after user bootstrap (not DB default)
- Grant amount is config-driven and versioned in migration/runbook docs to keep rollout deterministic

### Mapping from Supabase

- `profiles` -> `users`
- `user_app_subscriptions` (where `app_name='clanker'`) -> `subscriptions`
- `clanker_characters` -> `characters`
- `clanker_messages` -> `messages`
- RPC function logic -> transactional service methods in Functions

## Identity Model (Canonical Key)

- Canonical identity for all app-domain reads/writes is Firebase UID (`firebase_uid`).
- Existing Supabase UUID values are migration-only source artifacts.
- Any transitional mapping table is temporary and removed after cutover validation.

